        <txttip left="720" top="317" right="933" bottom="506" content="IP Address Planning&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;VLAN 10: 10.0.1.0/26&#x0D;&#x0A;    PC1: 10.0.1.1/26&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;VLAN 20: 10.0.1.64/26&#x0D;&#x0A;    PC2: 10.0.1.65/26&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;VLAN 100: 10.0.1.128/26&#x0D;&#x0A;  Server: 10.0.1.129/26" fontname="Consolas" fontstyle="0" editsize="120" txtcolor="-16777216" txtbkcolor="-4144960" charset="1" />
        <txttip left="14" top="332" right="526" bottom="483" content="Interface   Type    PVID    Tagged           Untagged&#x0D;&#x0A;SW1-G0/0/1  Hybrid  10                       1,10,100&#x0D;&#x0A;SW1-G0/0/2  Hybrid  20                       1,20,100&#x0D;&#x0A;SW1-G0/0/3  Hybrid   1      10,20,100&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;SW2-G0/0/1  Hybrid  10                       1,10,20,100&#x0D;&#x0A;SW2-G0/0/3  Hybrid  100     10,20,100&#x0D;&#x0A;" fontname="Consolas" fontstyle="0" editsize="120" txtcolor="-16777216" txtbkcolor="-4144960" charset="1" />
        <txttip left="4" top="515" right="1151" bottom="666" content="Requirements:&#x0D;&#x0A;1. Configure device names and IP addresses for each device&#x0D;&#x0A;2. Configure IP addresses and VLANs according to the above reference tables.&#x0D;&#x0A;3. Using ping utility, test connectivity between each device to each other device. Is there communication? Analyse the result.&#x0D;&#x0A;4. Capture ping(ICMP) frames at G0/0/1 of SW1 and G0/0/3 of SW1. Through WireShark, compare the captured frame encapsulations.&#x0D;&#x0A;   Be sure to run a ping from PC1 to the Server to capture packets. What do you notice about the capture result?&#x0D;&#x0A;   Answer: yes  i got result from ping but encapsulation frames from two side are different&#x0D;&#x0A;5. Save your configurations on all devices and save the topology as &apos;Name-UserID-VLANlab2&apos;" fontname="Consolas" fontstyle="0" editsize="120" txtcolor="-16777216" txtbkcolor="-4144960" charset="1" />
